A Theory for Semantic Communications
Shuai Ma, Youlong Wu, Huayan Qi, Hang Li, Guangming Shi, Fellow, IEEE ,
Yong Liang, and Naofal Al-Dhahir, Fellow, IEEE
Abstract
Semantic communications, as one of the potential key technologies of the sixth generation com-
munications (6G), has attracted research interest from both academia and industry. However, semantic
communication is still in its infancy and it faces many challenges, such as semantic information deﬁnition
and semantic communication measurement. To address these challenges, we investigate uniﬁed semantic
information measures and semantic channel coding theorem. Speciﬁcally, to address the shortcoming
